children.name: Text Description
children.characters: Sliders are an interactive and visual way to select values or range of values.

children.name: Section title / Heading 3
children.characters: How to Set the Slider Value

children.name: Text
children.characters:
The slider’s value is set by the Auto Layout “Spacing between items” property of a specific layer. This may seem like a weird way to move a dot along a line, but it’s the only way to let you can move a nested object within a component’s instance

To set the location of the dot (or value), find the “ Dot Value” Auto Layout layer, inspect the Auto Layout properties on the right, and adjust the “Spacing between items” property (]I[ icon) up and down in value.

children.name: Text
children.characters:
The range slider’s value is set by two different Auto Layout “Spacing between items” properties. 

To set the location of the first dot, find the “1st Dot Value” Auto Layout layer, inspect the Auto Layout properties on the right, and adjust the “Spacing between items” property (]I[ icon) up and down in value.

To set the location of the second dot, find the “2nd Dot Value” Auto Layout layer and do the same thing.

children.name: Section title / Heading 3
children.characters: How to Change the Slider’s Color

children.name: Text
children.characters:
The default processColor is Teal 70. 

To change, select the instance, locate this color in the Select Colors property, and change the color.
